Ah! There's the problem! Lines 29-33 are importing directly from the source files using relative paths:

```typescript
import { ClassificationPipeline } from '../../../classification-engine/src/pipeline/classification-pipeline';
import { ConfigurationLoader } from '../../../classification-engine/src/config/config-loader';
import type { CategoryConfiguration } from '../../../classification-engine/src/types/category-configuration';
import type { EmailMessage } from '../../../classification-engine/src/types/email-message';
import type { ClassificationResult } from '../../../classification-engine/src/types/classification-result';
```

These should be importing from the package name `@gmail-automation/classification-engine` instead, which would resolve to the dist files when using TypeScript project references.

This is the root cause of the TS6305 error - TypeScript sees that email-processor is importing from classification-engine's source files, but in a composite project, it expects imports to go through the package exports (which point to the built dist files).

I need to change all these imports in email-processor to use the package name instead of relative paths.

